        "fontWeight": "900",
        "fontSize": 26
      }
    },
    {
      "text": "This is the Korean Peninsula.",
      "fadeIn": [130, 160],
      "fadeOut": [210, 215],
      "style": {
        "bottom": 250,
        "background": "rgba(0,0,0,0.55)",
        "border": "1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.12)",
        "padding": "10px 32px"
      },
      "spanStyle": {
        "fontFamily": "'Inter', 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif",
        "fontWeight": 400,
        "fontSize": 26
      }
    },
    {
      "text": "Home to over 75 million people.",
      "fadeIn": [215, 250],
      "fadeOut": [355, 365],
      "style": {
        "bottom": 280
      }
    },
    {
      "text": "But why are there two Koreas?",
      "fadeIn": [365, 400],
      "fadeOut": [510, 515],
      "style": {
        "bottom": 280
      }
    },
    {
      "text": "Well, the answer, as always, is history.",
      "fadeIn": [515, 545],
      "fadeOut": [600, 605],
      "style": {
        "bottom": 280
      }
    },
    {
      "text": "For centuries, Korea existed as a single kingdom.",
      "fadeIn": [605, 640],
      "fadeOut": [780, 785],
      "style": {
        "bottom": 280
      }
    },
    {
      "text": "But the peninsula remained united.",
      "fadeIn": [785, 820],
      "fadeOut": [900, 905],
      "style": {
        "bottom": 280
      }
    },
    {
      "text": "Then, another country showed up.",
      "fadeIn": [905, 940],
      "fadeOut": [1020, 1022],
      "style": {
        "bottom": 280
      }
    },
    {
      "text": "Japan.",
      "fadeIn": [1022, 1045],
      "fadeOut": [1080, 1082],
      "style": {
        "bottom": 280
      }
    },
    {
      "text": "Japan takes control of Korea.",
      "fadeIn": [1085, 1120],
      "style": {
        "bottom": 280
      }
    }
  ],
